The numbers are placed on a hexagonal spiral.  
For a cell with axial coordinates \((x,y)\)

* its ring is \(k=\max(|x|,|y|,|x+y|)\);
* the first number of ring \(k\) is \(N_{k-1}+1\) where \(N_k = 1+3k(k+1)\);
* moving from the start \((k,0)\) around the ring follows the six directions  

\[
\text{NW},\; \text{W},\; \text{SW},\; \text{SE},\; \text{E},\; \text{NE}
\]

with \(k\) steps on each of the first five sides and \(k-1\) on the last.

---

### 1.  Locate 2026  

Find its ring:
\[
N_{25}=1951,\qquad N_{26}=2107\quad\Longrightarrow\quad k=26 .
\]

The first number of ring 26 is \(1952\) at \((26,0)\).  
\(2026-1952 = 74\) steps from the start, which lies on the third side (SW) of the ring, 22 steps into that side.  

Hence the coordinates of 2026 are  

\[
(-26,4).
\]

---

### 2.  Coordinates of the six neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
E &: (-25,4) &\quad (k=25)\\
NE&: (-26,5) &\quad (k=26)\\
NW&: (-27,5) &\quad (k=27)\\
W &: (-27,4) &\quad (k=27)\\
SW&: (-26,3) &\quad (k=26)\\
SE&: (-25,3) &\quad (k=25)
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 3.  Convert each coordinate back to its number  

Using the same ring‑walk description:

| coordinate | ring \(k\) | side & step \(i\) | offset \(d\) | number |
|------------|------------|------------------|--------------|--------|
| \((-25,4)\) | 25 | side 2 (SW), \(i=21\) | \(d=2k+i=50+21=71\) | \(1802+71=1873\) |
| \((-26,5)\) | 26 | side 2 (SW), \(i=21\) | \(d=52+21=73\) | \(1952+73=2025\) |
| \((-27,5)\) | 27 | side 2 (SW), \(i=22\) | \(d=54+22=76\) | \(2108+76=2184\) |
| \((-27,4)\) | 27 | side 2 (SW), \(i=23\) | \(d=54+23=77\) | \(2108+77=2185\) |
| \((-26,3)\) | 26 | side 2 (SW), \(i=23\) | \(d=52+23=75\) | \(1952+75=2027\) |
| \((-25,3)\) | 25 | side 2 (SW), \(i=22\) | \(d=50+22=72\) | \(1802+72=1874\) |

Thus the six neighbours of 2026 are  

\[
1873,\;2025,\;2184,\;2185,\;2027,\;1874 .
\]

---

### 4.  Sum of the neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
1873+2025+2184+2185+2027+1874 &= 12168 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{12168}
\]
